Two-time Actor of the Year, Daniel K Daniel, popularly known as DKD is back in Nigeria. Popularly known for his AMVCA Best Actor award-winning role as Bossman in the movie A Soldier’s Story, DKD recently made his return to Nigeria after spending about four years sharpening his skills in the United States. While in the states, the AMAA 2016 Actor of the Year, was a part of multiple film productions, teaming up with ace producers and veteran actors in the diaspora and a few Hollywood productions, including, “The Drone that Saved Christmas” & “Bloodline of The Jewel”. DKD recently returned to Nigeria and has rekindled his relationship with Globacom after filming his 3rd TV commercial with the company. He has been spotted on the red Carpet at multiple high profile events, including the Glo Battle of the Year and The Blood Covenant premiere. He’s already working on new projects like the movie “Dear Sister”, produced by Etinosa Idemudia and “Yellows & Blacks” directed by Tchidi Chikere. It’s been rumoured that the two-time Actor of the Year is set to Star in Showmax original blockbuster production. 